<br>
Plus since the range check is done BOTH when you first start casting and when the song actually hits, any slight movement in the meantime means your song just missed.<br>
<br>
Unfortunately the short range will make it FAR more dangerous to use than other classes charms...you WILL get hit at least once or twice (per mob) every time you use it, and with the enormous amount of damage 70th level mobs do (especially in GoD and likely in OoW) that's probably enough to flatten the bard.  With the short duration this will make it nearly impossible to use even just to charm solo.<br>
<br>
I would suggest that at least 80 or 100 is a much more reasonable range, though increasing the mana cost somewhat would be also reasonable (though NOT to 300...I would say perhaps 150, or 200 max).  The mana cost increase would also help limit swarming possibility, and the increased damage potential of the pet makes increased mana appropriate.<br>
