<br>
I want to pull two mobs and hit one of them with my high level charm, and send it at the other mob. The group engages, we kill it, I break charm, and we kill my pet. <br>
<br>
It should have a decent mana cost and a semi-long reuse (5 minutes?), and, if the charm breaks, I should have similar aggro issues as a chanter does with charm break.<br>
<br>
This is not a charm I could use to swarm kite. Sure, I could do some pet/chant kiting stuff, and it'd speed things up a bit, but there's no way for me to rake in the mass xp as I used to at level 55 with werewolves in PoN. It's a CC tool, it's a spurt DPS tool, and it's fun. It's in no way as powerful as druid or chanter charming, but it puts charm back in the game for the high level bard, and I want that. <p><!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://umdrive.memphis.edu/jzastrow/ohmy/rivyn2.jpg "/><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccb9b><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://p201.ezboard.com/btheconcerthall.showUserPublicProfile?gid=lokalhost>lokalhost</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Minstrel</span><br>  Posts: 116<br> <font color=#330000>(6/9/04 11:45 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://p201.ezboard.com/ftheconcerthallbackstage.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=19466.topic&index=50>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.telusplanet.net/public/geckos/ebay/c21de157f92c72347310e5abf88a0900_avatar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ~</span><hr size=1> I'd think 300 mana/charm would be a minimum unless they cut the duration.  Consider 6k mana and ft15 you could swarm for some time before mana became an issue.   Add tribute FT and mana would be very little concern. <br>
